entries.title: Scroll of Menu Crashes List View
entries.description:
For recommendations when empty, I returned a SizedBox with no height, needs height for ListView.builder

The issue: when you use a Container or Widget without child and or without height property inside ListVIew The solution: Just give height property to Widget that inside ListView.

This is my code, that's worked for me

.......
body: ListView(
          shrinkWrap: true,
          children: <Widget>[
            Auth ? Container(height: 1): signUpWidget() , // Add height property to Container
            .....
            ......
          ]
       )

entries.title: Verrify all Sorts for all types are working correctly

entries.description:
Quantity :: If Zero returning 50%, which provided result of spliting items with a value in half and inserting zeros in the middle

* Also in getRanking().[expiration] when dates compared one day apart and divided to percent become less than a day and then equal in value, fixed by calculated percent change in seconds of time durration
